data.content:
Three known C# 13 breaking changes:

---

### 1. `Buffer.cs` — `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` is now an error
The compiler-synthesized `Equals`/`GetHashCode` only compared the first element, so C# 13 disallows this entirely. **Fix:** use a plain `struct`:

```csharp
[System.Runtime.CompilerServices.InlineArray(10)]
struct Buffer
{
    private int _element0;
}
```

---

### 2. `Generator.cs` — `stackalloc` in local function inside iterator is now an error
C# 13 closes the loophole that allowed unsafe code in sync local functions within iterators. **Fix:** extract the method out of the iterator:

```csharp
unsafe class DataGenerator
{
    IEnumerable<int> Generate()
    {
        yield return 1;
        Process();
    }

    static void Process()
    {
        int* p = stackalloc int[10];
        // ... work with pointer
    }
}
```

---

### 3. `Resolver.cs` — `Process([])` is now ambiguous
C# 13 added first-class implicit span conversions, so `[]` now matches **both** `ReadOnlySpan<int>` and `Span<object>`, causing ambiguity. **Fix:** disambiguate explicitly:

```csharp
Process(ReadOnlySpan<int>.Empty);
// or
Process((ReadOnlySpan<int>)[]);
```
